{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"927c8d60-1bd0-43d6-835d-66d865bfd2f9","content":"No files found in the working directory. I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` to enable compiled bindings:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" ?>\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"Theme\" />\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Notifications\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Font Size\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Key change:** The `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute tells the XAML compiler the type of the BindingContext, so all `{Binding ...}` expressions are validated at compile time.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n1. **Enable compiled bindings warnings as errors** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is emitted when a binding path can't be resolved against the declared `x:DataType`.\n\n2. **What gets caught:** If you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), the build will fail with an error instead of silently failing at runtime.\n\n3. **Opting out locally** — if you need a runtime binding on a specific element (e.g., binding to a parent or ancestor), use `x:DataType=\"\"` to disable compiled bindings for that subtree:\n\n```xml\n<Label Text=\"{Binding Source={RelativeSource AncestorType={x:Type ContentPage}}, Path=Title}\"\n       x:DataType=\"\" />\n```\n\nThis gives you type-safe bindings with compile-time verification for misspelled or missing properties.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"98112b63-ea44-4cf9-aad8-51dd0aae29b5","outputTokens":602,"requestId":"9428:2A1132:13C397A:1624D54:6A066F82"},"id":"3f85235c-5d98-4405-a346-f44ce31cdc37","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:57:50.072Z","parentId":"d3bd2cba-ab67-4726-b6b8-f9bc7f747b7d"}
